The principles of the general and special part of the law of obligations and the relationships between them. Contractual and non-contractual obligations. An overview of different types of contracts and the practical possibilities for using them. The general principles of procedural law underpinning the settlement of civil disputes. The rights and obligations of the parties to the proceedings and the related legal consequences.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to provide the student with an understanding of the principles of the general and special part of the law of obligations and the relationships between them as well as the main types of contracts relating to the studied speciality, the possibilities for settling civil disputes and the consequences arising from the compulsory execution of obligations.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  1) knows the main institutes of the law of obligations; 2) knows the general principles of the law of obligations; 3) knows the main terms and conditions of the most relevant types of contracts related to the studied speciality and the bases for differentiating between them; 4) knows the relationships between the general and special part of the law of obligations and the specifics of their application; 5) knows the extrajudicial and judicial possibilities for settling civil disputes; 6) knows the main concepts of a civil procedure and enforcement procedure; 7) knows, how to apply their knowledge at medium level in the settlement of civil disputes, differentiate between contractual and non-contractual relationships of the law of obligations, and analyse the main contracts.
